---
source: crates/carta/tests/golden_e2e.rs
expression: output
---
A single letter that is also a numeral defaults to alphabetic:

\begin{enumerate}
\def\labelenumi{\alph{enumi}.}
\setcounter{enumi}{2}
\tightlist
\item
  third by letter
\item
  fourth by letter
\end{enumerate}

The letter i alone is read as a roman numeral:

\begin{enumerate}
\def\labelenumi{\roman{enumi}.}
\tightlist
\item
  one
\item
  two
\end{enumerate}
